main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed from Goose AFB, Labrador on February 7, 1953, following some earlier sightings on May 2, 1953.
interesting points: The objects were sighted on a circular course at an estimated altitude of 10,000 feet., They remained visible for approximately 45 minutes before disappearing., Photographic analysis confirmed that the objects were not conventional aircraft., An F-94 pilot was scrambled but could not make visual contact., Witnesses described two luminous objects approximately 500 yards in length.
witness description: AFB controllers, an F-94 pilot, and commercial airline pilots reported the sightings.
